Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g}(no need to peel) into 3cm chunks and pop onto a large
#baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes} - you'll roast them
for longer once you've crushed them.

Meanwhile, quarter the @pear{1} lengthways (no need to peel), remove the core
and cut into thin wedges lengthways.

Trim and halve the @green beans{80%g}. Roughly chop the @walnuts{20}.

Quarter the @cooked beetroot{250%g} and cut into wedges.

> TIP: Wear gloves when handling the beetroot to avoid staining your hands.

In a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @wholegrain mustard{17%g},
@balsamic vinegar{24%ml}, @sugar{1/2%candy for the dressing} and
@olive oil{1.5%tbsp for the dressing}. Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}, then set your dressing aside.

When the potatoes have cooked for 20 mins, remove them from the oven. Use the
bottom of a #bowl{} or #pot{} to lightly crush each potato.

Drizzle the smashed potatoes with more @olive oil{} and return to the top shelf
of your oven until golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Pop the beetroot and pear slices onto another lightly oiled baking tray in a
single layer.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until tender, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove
and set aside.

While everything roasts, boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a
#saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Bring back to the boil, then add the beans and cook until just tender,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and rinse under cold water.

> TIP: Running the beans under cold water will keep them vibrant.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and green beans
to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Share your dressed salad between #serving bowls{} and add the smashed potatoes,
roasted pear and beetroot.

Crumble over the @goat's cheese{75%g} and scatter with the walnuts to finish.

Enjoy!